						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Achalēśvara shrine in the south-east corner of the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>The beginning of this inscription is lost. On palaeographical considerations this is assignable to 11-12th centuries A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the sale of land, that was lying fallow, to the temple for reclamation and utilisation of the produce for the flower-garlands and other services to god Tiruvārūruḍaiyār, by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Vāyaṟṟūr, for a consideration of 60 <hi rend="italic">kāśu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
